21 Sep 2010 01:32






I find it interesting how many of you are harping on the "sex doll" interpretation. I had nothing of the sort in mind when I wrote it, but of course I can't prove that to anyone, so you'll go on believing whatever you want.

The "anatomically correct" comment is in the spirit of scientific completeness; the up-front implication is that this thing is not human, but that phrase is used to emphasize that it might have been once, or at least very closely resembles a human on the outside. It's also relevant for the medical exam log. It seems silly to exclude a detail like that just because some people choose to read something perverse into it.

Aside from that, pooryoric, I like your suggestion. I had originally conceived this SCP as having been "made" from a human, although I didn't want to spell that out for the readers but instead let them speculate on the possibility. Since so many people apparently want this to be a sex doll, maybe writing it as exactly that and instead focusing on how it came to be and the motivations of its creator would be more interesting. I'll keep it in mind for a revision if I decide to pursue this one further.







